headlines.description: Roland Griffin scored 22 points and Iona heated up in the second half to defeat Saint Peter's 86-77 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin has 22, Iona turns back Saint Peter's 86-77

headlines.description: Isaiah Reese scored 13 points, pulled down 10 rebounds and dished out seven assists and Malik Johnson added eight free throws down the stretch to lead Canisius to its fourth straight win, a 71-64 victory over Quinnipiac on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reese leads Canisius to 71-64 win over Quinnipiac

headlines.description: MaCio Teague scored 14 points, including UNC Asheville's last nine points, and his step-back 3-pointer from the wing with 4.4 seconds left gave the Bulldogs a 66-64 win over Radford on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Teague's late 3s send UNC Asheville past Radford 66-64

headlines.description: Sam McDaniel had 23 points and 12 rebounds as Louisiana-Monroe won its second overtime game in three days, upsetting Georgia State 90-82 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisiana-Monroe wins again in OT, beats Georgia St. 90-82

headlines.description: Kahlil Dukes scored 22 points, Marvin Prochet and Matt Scott each had double-doubles and Niagara pulled away in the second half to beat Fairfield 95-83 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Niagara pulls away in second half, beats Fairfield 95-83

headlines.description: Roddy Peters made 21 points while grabbing 12 rebounds and Tevon Saddler added 22 points as Nicholls overwhelmed Houston Baptist 94-67 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Peters has 21 as Nicholls thrashes Houston Baptist 94-67

headlines.description: Jamaal King scored 19 of his 25 points in the first half, Keith Braxton had 20 points and nine rebounds and St. Francis (Pa.) beat St. Francis (Brooklyn) 90-65 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: St. Francis (Pa.) beats St. Francis (Brooklyn) 90-65

headlines.description: RaySean Scott scored a career-high 21 points and Florida Gulf Coast became the first team in the country this season to clinch a league title, beating South Carolina Upstate 88-71 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: FGCU clinches A-Sun title with 88-71 win over SC Upstate

headlines.description: John Davis scored 13 points, Daniel Fowler had 12 and Furman defeated Wofford 76-52 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Furman has big runs to dump Wofford 76-52

headlines.description: James Scott and Nick Masterson scored 20 points apiece and Kennesaw State beat Jacksonville 78-54 on Saturday, for its third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scott, Masterson lead, Kennesaw St. beats Jacksonville 78-54

headlines.description: Chris Clemons knocked down five 3-pointers and scored 25 points as Campbell took over sole possession of third place in the Big South Conference by cruising past Longwood, 88-54 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Campbell alone in 3rd in Big South, beats Longwood 88-54

headlines.description: Kevin Hervey had 33 points, eight rebounds and four blocks as UT Arlington held on to beat Texas State 70-68 in overtime on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hervey has 33 points, UT Arlington holds off Texas St. in OT

headlines.description: Jermaine Marrow totaled 27 points, six rebounds and six assists to lead Hampton to an 82-52 wire-to-wire victory over Norfolk State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marrow leads Hampton to 82-52 romp over Norfolk State

headlines.description: Shannon Bogues scored a career-best 35 points, making 6 of 8 from long range, as Stephen F. Austin thrashed Northwestern State 97-50 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogues scores 35 as SF Austin romps past NW State 97-50

headlines.description: Denzel Mahoney had 27 points, including a game-tying 3-pointer at the end of regulation, and Southeast Missouri State beat Tennessee-Martin 81-77 in overtime on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: SE Missouri State beats Tenn.-Martin 81-77 in OT

headlines.description: Ryan Kemrite and Elijah Cuffee had 15 points each and Liberty withstood Gardner-Webb down the stretch for a 77-65 win on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Liberty holds off Gardner-Webb 77-65

headlines.description: John Dewey III stole an inbound pass and fed Christopher Galbreath Jr. for a layup in the final seconds as Sam Houston State took a 71-69 win over Lamar in Southland Conference play on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sam Houston St. slips past Lamar 71-69 in final seconds

headlines.description: Alex Thompson and Demetrius Denzel-Dyson combined to score 44 points as Samford shot better than 67 percent from the field to fly past The Citadel, 116-103 in a Southern Conference game on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hot-shooting Samford blows past The Citadel, 116-103

headlines.description: Travin Thibodeaux had 16 points and Bryson Robinson added 15 as New Orleans rolled to a 62-53 win over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: New Orleans rolls to 62-53 win over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi

headlines.description: Mitchell Hahn scored 21 points and Daniel Norl added 19 points and Omaha beat Fort Wayne on the strength of 12 3-pointers for 90-85 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hahn, Norl send carry Omaha past Fort Wayne 90-85

headlines.description: Khalil Ahmad had 31 points and Kyle Allman added 21 and Cal State Fullerton made five free throws down the stretch to seal a 68-66 win over UC Davis on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cal State Fullerton holds off UC Davis for 68-66 win

headlines.description: Zach Braxton scored a career-high 25 points and tied a career high with 13 rebounds and Weber State beat Northern Colorado 71-66 in overtime on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Braxton, Harding lift Weber St. past N. Colorado 71-66 in OT

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "I’m getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. It’s a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how I’m going to dictate how my team wins. … It’s a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... It’s a process. Right now, it’s tough."
